00:01:34.028 --> 00:01:36.631 position:27% line:5% align:start
[ Waves crashing,
birds chirping ]

00:01:56.116 --> 00:01:58.820 position:33% line:89% align:start
[ Bird coos ]

00:01:58.853 --> 00:02:07.562 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:02:07.595 --> 00:02:10.130 position:35% line:83% align:start
K: Everything appears
to be going well.

00:02:12.199 --> 00:02:15.302 position:5% line:83% align:start
Uncle, if you don't mind,
I'd like to ask --

00:02:15.335 --> 00:02:19.306 position:5% line:83% align:start
why did you choose Shitan,
of all people?

00:02:19.339 --> 00:02:23.111 position:5% line:83% align:start
His devotion to Yukimaru
runs far too deep.

00:02:23.143 --> 00:02:24.612 position:5% line:89% align:start
While he is my brother,

00:02:24.646 --> 00:02:29.182 position:5% line:83% align:start
I do have grave concerns
over his attachment to others.

00:02:29.216 --> 00:02:30.985 position:19% line:89% align:start
That's why he was chosen --

00:02:31.019 --> 00:02:35.455 position:19% line:83% align:start
to prevent him from falling
under the witch's influence.

00:02:35.489 --> 00:02:39.226 position:5% line:83% align:start
Yukimaru, then, may have already
fallen under the witch's spell.

00:02:39.259 --> 00:02:41.461 position:5% line:89% align:start
Is that what you suspect?

00:02:41.495 --> 00:02:44.565 position:19% line:83% align:start
It's at least a possibility
worth considering.

00:02:45.566 --> 00:02:48.201 position:47% line:83% align:start
On the evening
that <i>The Hope</i> went down,

00:02:48.235 --> 00:02:51.338 position:44% line:83% align:start
you were the one
who saved Yukimaru's life.

00:02:51.371 --> 00:02:54.742 position:10% line:83% align:start
Ever since, that boy looked up
to you as a big brother,

00:02:54.776 --> 00:02:58.378 position:24% line:83% align:start
even becoming a swordsman
to emulate you.

00:02:58.412 --> 00:03:03.450 position:27% line:83% align:start
K, do you think Yukimaru
has surpassed you in that skill?

00:03:07.588 --> 00:03:08.923 position:10% line:89% align:start
I can't be sure.

00:03:08.956 --> 00:03:12.760 position:5% line:83% align:start
Until we cross blades again,
there's no way to know.

00:03:16.130 --> 00:03:17.431 position:24% line:89% align:start
[ Metal clanging ]

00:03:17.464 --> 00:03:20.434 position:5% line:83% align:start
Girl: Shitan sensei,
it's time for my training.

00:03:20.467 --> 00:03:22.503 position:58% line:89% align:start
Coming.

00:03:24.072 --> 00:03:27.240 position:38% line:83% align:start
Orléans?
But that's in France, isn't it?

00:03:27.274 --> 00:03:29.010 position:7% line:83% align:start
Yeah, we were wrong
about it

00:03:29.043 --> 00:03:30.511 position:19% line:83% align:start
coming from
Libar-Oberstein.

00:03:30.545 --> 00:03:32.046 position:21% line:83% align:start
Turns out
it was carved there

00:03:32.080 --> 00:03:33.413 position:5% line:89% align:start
but mined in Orléans.

00:03:33.447 --> 00:03:36.851 position:19% line:83% align:start
The Burgermeister said
that was highly unusual.

00:03:36.884 --> 00:03:38.119 position:50% line:89% align:start
Is that all?

00:03:38.152 --> 00:03:39.787 position:35% line:83% align:start
Shitan: Well, there's
one more thing.

00:03:39.821 --> 00:03:41.522 position:21% line:83% align:start
It would appear the client
who commissioned it

00:03:41.556 --> 00:03:43.658 position:38% line:83% align:start
was the one and only
Joan of Arc.

00:03:43.691 --> 00:03:46.127 position:24% line:83% align:start
Wait. The one from
the Hundred Years War?

00:03:46.160 --> 00:03:49.130 position:5% line:83% align:start
Thing is, she was executed
five years before.

00:03:49.163 --> 00:03:52.399 position:50% line:83% align:start
Huh? O-Okay.
That is strange.

00:03:52.432 --> 00:03:55.136 position:10% line:83% align:start
It's not something we should
just accept at face value.

00:03:55.169 --> 00:03:57.605 position:33% line:83% align:start
But we can't
disprove it either.

00:03:57.638 --> 00:03:59.406 position:5% line:83% align:start
I guess that's true.
I can't really see

00:03:59.439 --> 00:04:01.542 position:5% line:83% align:start
what the old man would gain
from lying about it.

00:04:01.576 --> 00:04:05.613 position:16% line:83% align:start
Mm. Okay, but what if we
go there and it's a bust?

00:04:05.646 --> 00:04:06.714 position:27% line:89% align:start
I mean, it's far.

00:04:06.748 --> 00:04:09.349 position:52% line:83% align:start
Either way,
it seems our best path's

00:04:09.382 --> 00:04:10.885 position:41% line:83% align:start
wherever the wind's
blowing us,

00:04:10.918 --> 00:04:12.553 position:24% line:89% align:start
at least for now, anyway.

00:04:12.587 --> 00:04:15.288 position:21% line:83% align:start
Both: Us two seconds
is seconding.

00:04:15.322 --> 00:04:16.557 position:16% line:83% align:start
You can doubt
all you want,

00:04:16.591 --> 00:04:18.693 position:7% line:83% align:start
but Fenaska hasn't
led us astray yet.

00:04:18.726 --> 00:04:20.795 position:24% line:89% align:start
True! What he said.

00:04:20.828 --> 00:04:26.466 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:04:26.501 --> 00:04:29.570 position:27% line:83% align:start
All right, fine.
Let's go.

00:04:29.604 --> 00:04:31.172 position:19% line:83% align:start
We'll maintain a course
to the west,

00:04:31.205 --> 00:04:33.074 position:7% line:89% align:start
set in at Nantes for supplies,

00:04:33.107 --> 00:04:35.510 position:27% line:83% align:start
and then head up
the Lorient River.

00:04:35.543 --> 00:04:41.682 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:04:41.716 --> 00:04:47.922 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:04:47.955 --> 00:04:49.524 position:16% line:89% align:start
Are you sure this is it?

00:04:49.557 --> 00:04:51.491 position:13% line:77% align:start
Pretty sure.
So which hole is it?

00:04:51.526 --> 00:04:53.728 position:16% line:83% align:start
That I'm not
so sure about.

00:04:53.761 --> 00:04:55.630 position:21% line:83% align:start
But there's gotta be
over 100 of them.

00:04:55.663 --> 00:04:58.666 position:19% line:71% align:start
Yeah.
So what's the plan here,
Captain?

00:04:58.699 --> 00:04:59.867 position:21% line:89% align:start
No clue.

00:04:59.901 --> 00:05:02.103 position:41% line:83% align:start
Don't give me that.
You made us come here.

00:05:02.136 --> 00:05:03.370 position:7% line:89% align:start
Cut me some slack.

00:05:03.403 --> 00:05:04.739 position:16% line:83% align:start
The map I got
from the Burgermeister

00:05:04.772 --> 00:05:07.241 position:5% line:83% align:start
didn't mention anything
about all these holes.

00:05:07.275 --> 00:05:10.211 position:10% line:83% align:start
Fena, just pick one of them,
then we'll go.

00:05:10.244 --> 00:05:12.479 position:27% line:89% align:start
Wahh!

00:05:15.382 --> 00:05:16.884 position:30% line:89% align:start
There they are.

00:05:16.918 --> 00:05:19.687 position:10% line:83% align:start
I think I found those Asians
you were looking for.

00:05:19.720 --> 00:05:20.621 position:52% line:89% align:start
Nice work.

00:05:20.655 --> 00:05:21.756 position:44% line:83% align:start
And do they look
like a bunch

00:05:21.789 --> 00:05:25.492 position:27% line:83% align:start
that could give our crew
trouble?

00:05:25.526 --> 00:05:28.996 position:10% line:83% align:start
To be honest, the girl looks
about as harmless as a kitten.

00:05:30.665 --> 00:05:33.234 position:21% line:83% align:start
What's the situation
down there?

00:05:33.267 --> 00:05:35.703 position:44% line:83% align:start
We spotted them.
Do we move in?

00:05:35.736 --> 00:05:36.637 position:38% line:89% align:start
Go ahead.

00:05:36.671 --> 00:05:38.639 position:52% line:83% align:start
All right,
we're moving out!

00:05:38.673 --> 00:05:40.508 position:38% line:89% align:start
All: Aye!

00:05:42.210 --> 00:05:46.981 position:24% line:89% align:start
Mm. Oh. Oh. Mm. Oh.

00:05:47.014 --> 00:05:49.482 position:33% line:89% align:start
[ Muttering ]

00:05:53.688 --> 00:05:56.257 position:38% line:83% align:start
[ Sighs ]
I really have no clue.

00:05:56.290 --> 00:05:57.925 position:13% line:89% align:start
What should I do, Yukimaru?

00:05:57.959 --> 00:05:59.927 position:35% line:83% align:start
We should first start
by getting inside.

00:05:59.961 --> 00:06:02.830 position:7% line:83% align:start
Then if we determine it's safe,
we split into teams.

00:06:02.864 --> 00:06:05.432 position:35% line:83% align:start
Good idea.
I hadn't thought of that.

00:06:05.465 --> 00:06:07.201 position:19% line:83% align:start
Then let's start there,
everyone.

00:06:07.235 --> 00:06:10.137 position:52% line:83% align:start
Both: Whoa!
That was fast.

00:06:10.171 --> 00:06:11.305 position:19% line:89% align:start
It's stuck.

00:06:11.339 --> 00:06:14.441 position:35% line:89% align:start
[ Grunts ]

00:06:14.474 --> 00:06:16.277 position:13% line:89% align:start
Yeah, this one won't budge.

00:06:16.310 --> 00:06:18.279 position:27% line:83% align:start
I think we gotta
pull out these boards.

00:06:18.312 --> 00:06:20.748 position:30% line:83% align:start
Makaba, didn't you have
a nail extractor?

00:06:20.781 --> 00:06:22.283 position:30% line:89% align:start
[ Clattering ]

00:06:22.316 --> 00:06:24.518 position:24% line:89% align:start
Both: Anybody home?

00:06:27.054 --> 00:06:28.890 position:55% line:89% align:start
[ Gasps ]

00:06:28.923 --> 00:06:31.025 position:27% line:89% align:start
Whoa!

00:06:31.058 --> 00:06:32.560 position:47% line:89% align:start
What on Earth?

00:06:32.593 --> 00:06:35.630 position:19% line:83% align:start
My gut says
this is no ordinary mine.

00:06:35.663 --> 00:06:43.504 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:06:43.537 --> 00:06:46.874 position:10% line:77% align:start
Is this a temple?
Possibly.

00:06:46.908 --> 00:06:49.176 position:30% line:83% align:start
Looks like you may have
hit the jackpot again.

00:06:49.210 --> 00:06:51.712 position:19% line:89% align:start
This place sure is strange.

00:06:52.813 --> 00:06:53.581 position:30% line:89% align:start
Mm?

00:06:53.614 --> 00:06:55.516 position:24% line:89% align:start
What is it, Makaba?

00:06:55.549 --> 00:06:57.952 position:5% line:89% align:start
I see a door up ahead.

00:06:57.985 --> 00:06:59.587 position:5% line:89% align:start
If this is a temple,

00:06:59.620 --> 00:07:02.390 position:7% line:83% align:start
maybe it could lead
to the cemetery.

00:07:02.422 --> 00:07:04.125 position:21% line:83% align:start
What now?
We go.

00:07:04.158 --> 00:07:06.060 position:7% line:77% align:start
The left or right?
Left.

00:07:06.093 --> 00:07:07.528 position:21% line:83% align:start
Based on?
My gut.

00:07:07.561 --> 00:07:10.497 position:16% line:83% align:start
Fair enough.
Your gut's been pretty reliable.

00:07:10.531 --> 00:07:12.333 position:7% line:83% align:start
All right, Captain.
Don't mind me.

00:07:12.366 --> 00:07:13.601 position:16% line:83% align:start
I'm gonna go
hold up the rear.

00:07:13.634 --> 00:07:15.670 position:19% line:83% align:start
Good luck!
[ Gasps ]

00:07:15.703 --> 00:07:24.946 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:07:24.979 --> 00:07:33.955 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:07:33.988 --> 00:07:36.424 position:47% line:77% align:start
Bodies left out
unburied.
Yeah.

00:07:36.456 --> 00:07:38.759 position:38% line:83% align:start
I see a lot of women
and children.

00:07:38.793 --> 00:07:40.962 position:5% line:83% align:start
Maybe they were driven in here
and took their lives,

00:07:40.995 --> 00:07:43.831 position:5% line:83% align:start
or maybe they were sick
with something and quarantined.

00:07:43.864 --> 00:07:46.067 position:10% line:83% align:start
Whatever it was,
it didn't end well.

00:07:46.100 --> 00:07:49.236 position:58% line:77% align:start
Karin:
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

00:07:49.270 --> 00:07:50.504 position:38% line:89% align:start
Stop it!

00:07:50.538 --> 00:07:52.273 position:52% line:83% align:start
Look away!
Nothing to see back here.

00:07:52.306 --> 00:07:53.774 position:35% line:83% align:start
This place is haunted
for sure.

00:07:53.808 --> 00:07:55.910 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'm telling you, my family
can sense these things.

00:07:55.943 --> 00:07:57.545 position:30% line:83% align:start
-Karin. Karin!
-What do you want?!

00:07:57.578 --> 00:08:00.581 position:27% line:89% align:start
[ Karin screams ]

00:08:00.614 --> 00:08:02.950 position:19% line:77% align:start
[ Indistinct shouting ]
Huh?

00:08:05.286 --> 00:08:07.822 position:44% line:83% align:start
Fena:
The tunnel branches again.

00:08:07.855 --> 00:08:11.525 position:61% line:83% align:start
Okay.
Eeny, meeny, miny, moe.

00:08:11.559 --> 00:08:14.228 position:47% line:83% align:start
Fena, go ahead.
Pick a path.

00:08:14.261 --> 00:08:17.164 position:19% line:83% align:start
Huh? This was a fluke.
Last time I guessed randomly.

00:08:17.198 --> 00:08:18.833 position:7% line:89% align:start
It doesn't matter.

00:08:18.866 --> 00:08:21.302 position:16% line:83% align:start
Your guesses have a tendency
to be correct.

00:08:21.335 --> 00:08:24.271 position:13% line:83% align:start
I agree. Go on.
Trust your gut.

00:08:24.305 --> 00:08:25.940 position:30% line:89% align:start
I-I'm not sure.

00:08:25.973 --> 00:08:29.777 position:13% line:83% align:start
I really wish you wouldn't
put me on the spot like this.

00:08:33.981 --> 00:08:36.283 position:38% line:89% align:start
[ Gasps ]

00:08:36.317 --> 00:08:40.154 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:08:40.187 --> 00:08:43.557 position:10% line:83% align:start
Fena, what is it?
Hey.

00:08:43.591 --> 00:08:44.692 position:35% line:89% align:start
The right.

00:08:44.725 --> 00:08:47.161 position:61% line:83% align:start
Huh?
You're sure?

00:08:47.194 --> 00:08:49.030 position:30% line:89% align:start
We take the right fork.

00:08:49.063 --> 00:08:55.369 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:08:55.403 --> 00:08:56.704 position:19% line:89% align:start
[ Grunts ]

00:08:58.272 --> 00:09:00.841 position:27% line:89% align:start
[ All grunting ]

00:09:00.875 --> 00:09:06.981 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:09:07.014 --> 00:09:10.484 position:47% line:83% align:start
Is it just me,
or is this place real spooky?

00:09:10.519 --> 00:09:12.987 position:24% line:83% align:start
Not like you to be
a scaredy cat, Shing.

00:09:13.020 --> 00:09:15.723 position:7% line:83% align:start
Why don't you come here and say
that to my face, Alveda?

00:09:15.756 --> 00:09:18.492 position:5% line:83% align:start
Knock it off, you guys.
[ Scoffs ]

00:09:18.527 --> 00:09:21.128 position:5% line:83% align:start
The two of them bicker
like a couple of children.

00:09:21.162 --> 00:09:23.064 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Sis.
-Mm?

00:09:23.097 --> 00:09:24.365 position:35% line:89% align:start
What is it?

00:09:24.398 --> 00:09:25.866 position:47% line:83% align:start
There's a fork
in the tunnel.

00:09:25.900 --> 00:09:27.802 position:33% line:83% align:start
[ Exclaims in French ]
Which way they go?

00:09:27.835 --> 00:09:29.603 position:16% line:83% align:start
Don't ask me.
How should I know?

00:09:29.637 --> 00:09:31.405 position:55% line:89% align:start
What now?

00:09:31.439 --> 00:09:34.241 position:41% line:83% align:start
-Mary?
-Aye-aye, Captain!

00:09:37.912 --> 00:09:40.614 position:33% line:71% align:start
They went to the left.
Good.
Thank you, Mary.

00:09:40.648 --> 00:09:43.484 position:19% line:83% align:start
Everyone, we go right.
Come on. Follow me!

00:09:43.518 --> 00:09:45.619 position:5% line:83% align:start
Anne, leave the card back here.
Understood?

00:09:45.653 --> 00:09:47.621 position:13% line:83% align:start
Shing, Alveda,
give her a hand.

00:09:47.655 --> 00:09:49.890 position:38% line:83% align:start
-Aye-aye!
-Aye-aye!

00:09:49.924 --> 00:09:52.693 position:33% line:83% align:start
-Mary, the...
-Oh, yeah, right!

00:09:52.726 --> 00:09:54.228 position:30% line:89% align:start
[ Mary grunts ]

00:09:54.261 --> 00:10:01.836 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:10:01.869 --> 00:10:09.243 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:10:09.276 --> 00:10:16.684 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:10:16.717 --> 00:10:18.953 position:41% line:83% align:start
Let's keep moving,
Yukimaru.

00:10:22.823 --> 00:10:24.258 position:61% line:83% align:start
Enju:
That's enough, Karin.

00:10:24.291 --> 00:10:26.528 position:30% line:83% align:start
You're, like, seriously
making it hard to walk.

00:10:26.561 --> 00:10:28.796 position:33% line:83% align:start
You shut up.
Take one step away from me,

00:10:28.829 --> 00:10:30.532 position:19% line:83% align:start
and I'll beat the snot
out of you.

00:10:30.565 --> 00:10:32.534 position:50% line:89% align:start
So annoying.

00:10:32.567 --> 00:10:35.202 position:19% line:83% align:start
She seems -- she seems
different somehow.

00:10:35.236 --> 00:10:36.437 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yes, definitely.

00:10:36.470 --> 00:10:38.405 position:47% line:83% align:start
She's suddenly
way more decisive.

00:10:38.439 --> 00:10:40.474 position:33% line:83% align:start
Maybe she's remembered
something.

00:10:40.509 --> 00:10:42.877 position:35% line:83% align:start
That wasn't
what I was asking you.

00:10:42.910 --> 00:10:48.282 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:10:48.315 --> 00:10:50.084 position:16% line:83% align:start
We should go
this way, Sis!

00:10:50.117 --> 00:10:51.185 position:44% line:89% align:start
Good work, Mary.

00:10:51.218 --> 00:10:52.753 position:50% line:83% align:start
I can always
count on you.

00:10:52.786 --> 00:10:55.156 position:52% line:83% align:start
Charlotte,
leave a mark for later.

00:10:55.189 --> 00:10:56.924 position:30% line:89% align:start
 <i>Oui, Capitan.</i>

00:11:02.463 --> 00:11:04.798 position:21% line:89% align:start
[ Footsteps echoing ]

00:11:07.735 --> 00:11:09.770 position:41% line:83% align:start
We've gone a pretty
long way down.

00:11:09.803 --> 00:11:11.272 position:5% line:89% align:start
The humidity's changed.

00:11:11.305 --> 00:11:14.008 position:5% line:83% align:start
Do you think that we could be
beneath the river?

00:11:14.041 --> 00:11:16.343 position:50% line:83% align:start
She's acting
really out of sorts.

00:11:16.377 --> 00:11:17.612 position:19% line:89% align:start
Who? Fena?

00:11:17.646 --> 00:11:19.313 position:13% line:83% align:start
You're reading
too much into it.

00:11:19.346 --> 00:11:20.615 position:7% line:89% align:start
What's up with you?

00:11:20.649 --> 00:11:22.116 position:50% line:89% align:start
[ Grumbles ]

00:11:24.185 --> 00:11:26.521 position:21% line:83% align:start
-Yukimaru, are you...
-Am I what?

00:11:26.555 --> 00:11:28.856 position:13% line:83% align:start
Are you in love
with Fena?

00:11:28.889 --> 00:11:31.526 position:55% line:83% align:start
Come on.
Don't be ridiculous.

00:11:31.560 --> 00:11:34.862 position:7% line:83% align:start
I only made an observation that
she's not acting like herself.

00:11:34.895 --> 00:11:36.397 position:30% line:89% align:start
You're reading into it.

00:11:36.430 --> 00:11:37.865 position:5% line:89% align:start
Spoken like a true virgin.

00:11:37.898 --> 00:11:41.302 position:19% line:83% align:start
-Did you say something?
-Not a word.

00:11:52.647 --> 00:12:00.689 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:12:00.721 --> 00:12:02.489 position:44% line:89% align:start
Fena, is this it?

00:12:02.524 --> 00:12:03.757 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yes.

00:12:03.791 --> 00:12:05.893 position:52% line:83% align:start
How did you
know the way?

00:12:05.926 --> 00:12:08.429 position:7% line:89% align:start
Because I've been here before.

00:12:08.462 --> 00:12:10.831 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Huh?
-I figured as much.

00:12:10.864 --> 00:12:13.200 position:5% line:83% align:start
It's as Master Yukihisa
surmised.

00:12:13.234 --> 00:12:15.369 position:13% line:83% align:start
Fena's memories
have been locked away,

00:12:15.402 --> 00:12:17.071 position:21% line:83% align:start
buried in
her subconscious.

00:12:17.104 --> 00:12:18.772 position:5% line:83% align:start
But encountering sights
and smells

00:12:18.806 --> 00:12:21.408 position:5% line:83% align:start
of places from her past
is reawakening them.

00:12:21.442 --> 00:12:22.843 position:19% line:89% align:start
Did any memory surface

00:12:22.876 --> 00:12:24.979 position:27% line:83% align:start
about how we open
this monster of a door?

00:12:25.012 --> 00:12:27.682 position:24% line:83% align:start
Not even Makaba's muscles
could budge this thing.

00:12:27.716 --> 00:12:32.253 position:24% line:83% align:start
Well, maybe there's
a hidden key or something?

00:12:32.286 --> 00:12:35.122 position:24% line:89% align:start
[ Stone scraping ]

00:12:35.155 --> 00:12:44.566 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:12:44.599 --> 00:12:47.401 position:33% line:89% align:start
[ All gasp ]

00:12:47.434 --> 00:12:48.503 position:61% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:12:51.238 --> 00:12:53.675 position:38% line:89% align:start
[ Thud ]

00:12:53.708 --> 00:12:56.076 position:33% line:89% align:start
[ Rumbling ]

00:12:57.478 --> 00:12:59.346 position:38% line:89% align:start
[ Thud ]

00:13:00.715 --> 00:13:04.118 position:33% line:89% align:start
[ Rumbling ]

00:13:08.723 --> 00:13:10.592 position:30% line:83% align:start
Fens, don't go in there
without us.

00:13:10.625 --> 00:13:13.294 position:21% line:83% align:start
Yukimaru,
don't try to stop her.

00:13:13.327 --> 00:13:14.928 position:55% line:89% align:start
Why not?

00:13:16.598 --> 00:13:17.766 position:50% line:89% align:start
[ Grumbles ]

00:13:17.798 --> 00:13:20.100 position:27% line:89% align:start
[ Water rushing ]

00:13:25.239 --> 00:13:27.107 position:47% line:89% align:start
Oh.

00:13:31.278 --> 00:13:33.447 position:27% line:83% align:start
Touch your torch
to that basin there.

00:13:33.480 --> 00:13:35.349 position:30% line:89% align:start
Mm?

00:13:48.062 --> 00:13:51.498 position:19% line:89% align:start
[ Singing in Japanese ]

00:13:51.533 --> 00:13:58.472 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:13:58.506 --> 00:14:05.346 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:14:05.379 --> 00:14:12.119 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:14:12.152 --> 00:14:14.488 position:19% line:83% align:start
[ Grunts ]
What is this?

00:14:14.522 --> 00:14:17.625 position:21% line:89% align:start
[ Singing continues ]

00:14:17.659 --> 00:14:24.498 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:14:24.532 --> 00:14:31.305 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:14:31.338 --> 00:14:37.945 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:14:37.978 --> 00:14:40.414 position:41% line:83% align:start
So, is it just me,
or did nothing change?

00:14:40.447 --> 00:14:42.049 position:30% line:89% align:start
I-I don't know.

00:14:42.082 --> 00:14:43.852 position:10% line:83% align:start
I think the light might have
gotten a little bit brighter.

00:14:43.884 --> 00:14:46.220 position:19% line:83% align:start
-Yeah. A little, right?
-Mm.

00:14:50.558 --> 00:14:52.794 position:61% line:83% align:start
Okay,
so what do we do now?

00:14:52.827 --> 00:14:53.927 position:44% line:89% align:start
Guess we could...

00:14:53.961 --> 00:14:56.564 position:38% line:83% align:start
-Oh, wow.
-Hmm?

00:14:56.598 --> 00:14:59.333 position:24% line:83% align:start
I can see something
in there.

00:14:59.366 --> 00:15:01.235 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Huh?
-What?

00:15:01.268 --> 00:15:04.338 position:13% line:83% align:start
-What do you think that is?
-Let me see.

00:15:04.371 --> 00:15:09.577 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:15:09.611 --> 00:15:10.978 position:44% line:89% align:start
What?

00:15:11.011 --> 00:15:14.181 position:21% line:83% align:start
It kind of looks like
a bunch of scratches.

00:15:14.214 --> 00:15:15.449 position:19% line:89% align:start
Scratches?

00:15:15.482 --> 00:15:16.818 position:7% line:89% align:start
From wear and tear?

00:15:16.851 --> 00:15:19.621 position:19% line:83% align:start
No, these markings are
too precise to be random

00:15:19.654 --> 00:15:21.455 position:19% line:89% align:start
or naturally occurring.

00:15:23.190 --> 00:15:26.828 position:5% line:83% align:start
It is striped in a way that's
invisible to the naked eye.

00:15:26.861 --> 00:15:29.496 position:35% line:83% align:start
-[ Gasps ]
-Hmm. Karin.

00:15:29.531 --> 00:15:32.466 position:21% line:83% align:start
Already ahead of you.
Give me a second.

00:15:34.769 --> 00:15:37.337 position:21% line:89% align:start
Hang on. Are those...

00:15:40.742 --> 00:15:42.476 position:5% line:83% align:start
Karin: I need a brush
and some ink.

00:15:42.510 --> 00:15:45.045 position:5% line:89% align:start
I gotta write this down!

00:15:45.078 --> 00:15:47.948 position:21% line:83% align:start
[ Tambourine shaking
at intervals ]

00:16:04.666 --> 00:16:12.674 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:16:12.707 --> 00:16:20.748 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:16:20.782 --> 00:16:23.685 position:35% line:89% align:start
La Pucelle.

00:16:23.718 --> 00:16:26.987 position:35% line:83% align:start
Blue water
and storm clouds.

00:16:30.692 --> 00:16:34.061 position:7% line:89% align:start
You called me here, didn't you?

00:16:34.094 --> 00:16:37.364 position:27% line:89% align:start
But why? Why me?!

00:16:37.397 --> 00:16:38.600 position:38% line:89% align:start
[ Gasps ]

00:16:41.335 --> 00:16:43.638 position:30% line:83% align:start
They're Roman numerals,
aren't they?

00:16:43.671 --> 00:16:45.673 position:5% line:83% align:start
There's a chance that
these numbers may point

00:16:45.707 --> 00:16:47.174 position:10% line:89% align:start
to a destination.

00:16:47.207 --> 00:16:49.176 position:13% line:83% align:start
Latitude?
Longitude?

00:16:49.209 --> 00:16:51.713 position:13% line:83% align:start
Karin: I bet that's exactly
what they are.

00:16:51.746 --> 00:16:53.180 position:16% line:83% align:start
Do you think
you'll be able

00:16:53.213 --> 00:16:54.782 position:16% line:83% align:start
to figure out
where it's pointing to?

00:16:54.816 --> 00:16:57.519 position:16% line:83% align:start
I could with the chronometer
we have back on the <i>Bonito.</i>

00:16:57.552 --> 00:16:59.621 position:41% line:83% align:start
It's a Harrison C4,
top of the line.

00:16:59.654 --> 00:17:02.189 position:5% line:83% align:start
Problem is, we don't know
the directions.

00:17:02.222 --> 00:17:04.124 position:33% line:83% align:start
North, south,
east, west.

00:17:04.157 --> 00:17:05.827 position:5% line:89% align:start
Without more specifics,

00:17:05.860 --> 00:17:07.962 position:13% line:83% align:start
there are four
potential locations.

00:17:07.996 --> 00:17:10.932 position:24% line:83% align:start
We'd have to travel
to a lot of places.

00:17:10.965 --> 00:17:13.233 position:5% line:83% align:start
I'd wager there's a clue
that could help us

00:17:13.267 --> 00:17:15.035 position:5% line:89% align:start
in Fena's -- ah -- huh?

00:17:17.772 --> 00:17:19.941 position:5% line:89% align:start
W-What's wrong, Yukimaru?

00:17:19.974 --> 00:17:22.075 position:52% line:89% align:start
She's gone.

00:17:22.109 --> 00:17:24.812 position:19% line:83% align:start
Who's gone?
Do you mean Fena?

00:17:24.846 --> 00:17:27.815 position:44% line:83% align:start
Fena!
Where are you?

00:17:27.849 --> 00:17:29.684 position:27% line:89% align:start
Fena!

00:17:29.717 --> 00:17:31.619 position:44% line:89% align:start
Found her for ya.

00:17:34.121 --> 00:17:37.625 position:35% line:83% align:start
-Yukimaru!
-Fena!

00:17:37.659 --> 00:17:39.694 position:44% line:89% align:start
Stop right there.

00:17:39.727 --> 00:17:45.365 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:17:45.399 --> 00:17:47.902 position:35% line:83% align:start
Now, then,
if you'd be so kind,

00:17:47.936 --> 00:17:51.471 position:27% line:83% align:start
how about we drop
those nasty little toys?

00:17:51.506 --> 00:17:55.643 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:17:55.677 --> 00:17:57.244 position:33% line:89% align:start
Are you deaf?

00:17:57.277 --> 00:17:58.913 position:27% line:83% align:start
Did you not hear
what our boss said,

00:17:58.947 --> 00:18:01.716 position:24% line:89% align:start
little archer girl?

00:18:01.749 --> 00:18:04.451 position:24% line:89% align:start
[ Fena whimpering ]

00:18:04.484 --> 00:18:06.320 position:41% line:89% align:start
Shitan!

00:18:06.353 --> 00:18:11.458 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:18:11.491 --> 00:18:15.597 position:16% line:83% align:start
[ Chuckles ]
And you, little pipsqueak.

00:18:15.630 --> 00:18:19.734 position:44% line:83% align:start
It's them again.
They're the ones from Bar-Baral.

00:18:19.767 --> 00:18:21.435 position:27% line:83% align:start
Now hand it over,
would you?

00:18:21.468 --> 00:18:25.138 position:19% line:83% align:start
Give me the coordinates
to El Dorado.

00:18:25.172 --> 00:18:26.874 position:35% line:89% align:start
El Dorado?

00:18:26.908 --> 00:18:28.843 position:16% line:83% align:start
What are you
talking about?

00:18:30.578 --> 00:18:32.279 position:19% line:83% align:start
If you know what's best
for you,

00:18:32.312 --> 00:18:33.313 position:21% line:89% align:start
you'll bring it over.

00:18:33.347 --> 00:18:35.282 position:16% line:89% align:start
The rest of you stay put.

00:18:35.315 --> 00:18:37.685 position:33% line:83% align:start
Yukimaru, don't worry.
I'll go.

00:18:37.719 --> 00:18:39.186 position:19% line:89% align:start
Be careful.

00:18:39.219 --> 00:18:40.955 position:30% line:83% align:start
Yeah, I think that goes
without saying.

00:18:40.989 --> 00:18:43.524 position:5% line:83% align:start
Yukimaru, if we hand it
over to them --

00:18:43.558 --> 00:18:45.359 position:41% line:89% align:start
We have no choice.

00:18:45.392 --> 00:18:47.895 position:21% line:89% align:start
If we make one false move,

00:18:47.929 --> 00:18:50.263 position:35% line:83% align:start
it'll put Fena's life
in danger.

00:18:59.073 --> 00:19:00.440 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmph.

00:19:00.474 --> 00:19:02.510 position:10% line:89% align:start
This ink isn't even dry yet.

00:19:02.543 --> 00:19:05.312 position:19% line:83% align:start
So I suppose that means
this isn't a fake.

00:19:05.345 --> 00:19:07.314 position:10% line:83% align:start
Unlike you guys,
we don't play dirty.

00:19:07.347 --> 00:19:10.551 position:5% line:83% align:start
Now, you better let Fena go
and beat it, you old hag.

00:19:11.686 --> 00:19:13.554 position:35% line:89% align:start
[ Grunts ]

00:19:13.588 --> 00:19:15.923 position:24% line:89% align:start
Karin!

00:19:15.957 --> 00:19:17.792 position:35% line:89% align:start
No! Stay right there.

00:19:17.825 --> 00:19:23.463 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:19:23.497 --> 00:19:26.067 position:33% line:83% align:start
So what do you want us
to do with them, Sis?

00:19:26.100 --> 00:19:27.802 position:10% line:83% align:start
Can we kill them?
Please?

00:19:27.835 --> 00:19:29.103 position:21% line:89% align:start
Don't even think it.

00:19:29.137 --> 00:19:31.606 position:19% line:83% align:start
Remember what happened
at Bar-Baral?

00:19:31.639 --> 00:19:35.743 position:38% line:83% align:start
These are
no ordinary mercenaries.

00:19:35.777 --> 00:19:37.111 position:13% line:89% align:start
Sorry to disappoint, folks,

00:19:37.145 --> 00:19:39.346 position:21% line:83% align:start
but I've no interest
in tussling with you.

00:19:39.379 --> 00:19:40.982 position:16% line:89% align:start
You can chain them down,

00:19:41.015 --> 00:19:43.417 position:30% line:83% align:start
but in the end,
wolves are still wolves.

00:19:43.450 --> 00:19:45.787 position:33% line:83% align:start
Get too close
and they'll bite you.

00:19:45.820 --> 00:19:49.724 position:35% line:83% align:start
I know you.
You are the Goblin Knights...

00:19:51.324 --> 00:19:53.493 position:7% line:83% align:start
...the masterful death brigade
that wiped out

00:19:53.528 --> 00:19:56.130 position:19% line:83% align:start
3,000 Spanish soldiers
in the blink of an eye

00:19:56.164 --> 00:19:57.665 position:16% line:89% align:start
at the Battle of Dumkuk,

00:19:57.699 --> 00:20:00.233 position:5% line:83% align:start
killers for hire who were feared
to be the incarnation

00:20:00.267 --> 00:20:02.503 position:24% line:89% align:start
of Lucifer himself.

00:20:02.537 --> 00:20:05.039 position:30% line:83% align:start
And you lot are
their descendants, aren't you?

00:20:05.073 --> 00:20:07.575 position:33% line:83% align:start
It's an honor
to make your acquaintance.

00:20:07.608 --> 00:20:09.376 position:41% line:89% align:start
But...

00:20:11.779 --> 00:20:13.781 position:16% line:77% align:start
Karin!
[ Gunshot ]

00:20:13.815 --> 00:20:16.718 position:47% line:83% align:start
Did we say that
any of you could move?

00:20:16.751 --> 00:20:19.053 position:19% line:89% align:start
[ Grunts ]

00:20:19.087 --> 00:20:21.155 position:33% line:89% align:start
[ Chuckles ]

00:20:21.189 --> 00:20:31.132 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:20:31.165 --> 00:20:33.868 position:24% line:83% align:start
Grace, are you sure
it's a good idea

00:20:33.901 --> 00:20:35.268 position:21% line:89% align:start
to leave them alive?

00:20:35.302 --> 00:20:37.471 position:41% line:83% align:start
You saw the skulls
on the way in, didn't you?

00:20:37.505 --> 00:20:39.306 position:47% line:83% align:start
There's no way
out of this place.

00:20:39.339 --> 00:20:40.575 position:47% line:83% align:start
If we block off
the entrance,

00:20:40.608 --> 00:20:42.744 position:30% line:83% align:start
they'll starve to death
eventually.

00:20:42.777 --> 00:20:44.145 position:27% line:89% align:start
I follow you now.

00:20:44.178 --> 00:20:46.480 position:27% line:83% align:start
Well, my little goblins,
I hate to be rude,

00:20:46.514 --> 00:20:48.149 position:50% line:83% align:start
but we really
must be going.

00:20:48.182 --> 00:20:50.151 position:44% line:83% align:start
Wait!
We gave you the location.

00:20:50.184 --> 00:20:51.485 position:24% line:89% align:start
Now hand over Fena!

00:20:51.519 --> 00:20:53.955 position:24% line:83% align:start
Apologies, but I'm afraid
I can't do that

00:20:53.988 --> 00:20:55.355 position:41% line:83% align:start
because apparently
we will need

00:20:55.388 --> 00:20:57.658 position:50% line:83% align:start
both the girl
and the coordinates.

00:20:57.692 --> 00:20:59.694 position:41% line:89% align:start
What?!

00:21:00.194 --> 00:21:01.929 position:21% line:89% align:start
[ Gasps ]

00:21:01.963 --> 00:21:03.296 position:21% line:89% align:start
Yukimaru!

00:21:03.330 --> 00:21:05.233 position:10% line:89% align:start
Help me, please!

00:21:05.265 --> 00:21:07.835 position:19% line:83% align:start
Let me go!
Let go!

00:21:07.869 --> 00:21:10.538 position:13% line:89% align:start
Guys! Yukimaru!

00:21:11.939 --> 00:21:13.074 position:38% line:89% align:start
Hey, Mary, let's go.

00:21:13.107 --> 00:21:14.575 position:21% line:89% align:start
Aye-aye!

00:21:17.879 --> 00:21:20.848 position:30% line:89% align:start
 <i>Adios, chicos.</i>

00:21:20.882 --> 00:21:28.556 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

00:21:28.589 --> 00:21:36.097 position:64% line:5% align:start
♪♪

